STEPS TO RUN:

1. Use split_wav2words.py to split a sample wav file to 3 phones wav files considering each phone at a time

2. Create split.ctl file using extracted split_wav directory

3. Run feature_extract.sh program to extract features for individual phoeme wav files

4. Java Speech Grammar Format (JSGF) files are already created in FSG_phoneme

5. Run jsgf2fsg.sh in FSG_3phoneme to convert from jsgf to fsg.

6. Run decode_words.py to decode to output_decoded_words.txt
